sentence: At the same time, Hungarian dominance faced challenges from the local majorities of Romanians in Transylvania and in the eastern Banat, Slovaks in today's Slovakia, and Croats and Serbs in the crown lands of Croatia and of Dalmatia (today's Croatia), in Bosnia and Herzegovina, and in the provinces known as the Vojvodina (today's northern Serbia).

positive_examples.sentence: This resulted in significant breakthroughs at the 2013 United Kingdom local elections, 2014 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom, and 2015 United Kingdom general election.
